{"sectionId":489,"sectionIdLiteral":"489","humanId":"lesson-85","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"ownlineNumber":"Lesson 85"},"annotation":"W-85","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text review-lesson review-2 lesson-85\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"489#0\"><p class=\"p-review-intro\"><span data-sentence-id=\"489#0:1\">Today‚Äôs review will cover these ideas:</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"489#1\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">69</span>) <b>My grievances hide the light of the world in me.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"489#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>My grievances show me what is not there, and hide from me what I would see.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Recognizing this, what do I want my grievances for?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>They keep me in darkness and hide the light.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Grievances and light cannot go together, but light and vision must be joined for me to see.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>To see, I must lay grievances aside.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>I want to see, and this will be the means by which I will succeed.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"489#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Specific applications for this idea might be made in these forms:</span></p> <p class=\"p-prayer\"><span data-sentence-id=\"489#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Let me not use this as a block to sight.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>The light of the world will shine all this away.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>I have no need for this.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>I want to see.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"489#3\"><p class=\"p-lesson-ref\"><span class=\"pnr\">3.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#3:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>(<span class=\"lref\">70</span>) <b>My salvation comes from me.</b></span></p> <p class=\"p-normal\"><span data-sentence-id=\"489#3:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Today I will recognize where my salvation is.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#3:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>It is in me because its Source is there.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#3:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>It has not left its Source, and so it cannot have left my mind.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#3:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>I will not look for it outside myself.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#3:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>It is not found outside and then brought in.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#3:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>But from within me it will reach beyond, and everything I see will but reflect the light that shines in me and in itself.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"489#4\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">4.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#4:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>These forms of the idea are suitable for more specific applications:</span></p> <p class=\"p-prayer\"><span data-sentence-id=\"489#4:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Let this not tempt me to look away from me for my salvation.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#4:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>I will not let this interfere with my awareness of the Source of my salvation.<br/></span> <span data-sentence-id=\"489#4:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>This has no power to remove salvation from me.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Today‚Äôs review will cover these ideas: (69) My grievances hide the light of the world in me. My grievances show me what is not there, and hide from me what I would see. Recognizing this, what do I","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 85: Review (69 and 70) | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†85 ‚ÄúReview (69 and 70)‚Äù: Today‚Äôs review will cover these ideas: (69) My grievances hide the light of the world in me. My‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":403,"slugs":["lesson-1","nothing-i-see-means-anything"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Review II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":484,"slugs":["review-ii","introduction"]}},{"label":"Lesson 85","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":489,"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-85"]}}],"mobileBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":403,"slugs":["lesson-1","nothing-i-see-means-anything"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Review II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":484,"slugs":["review-ii","introduction"]}},{"label":"Lesson 85","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":489,"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-85"]}}],"seoBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"A Course in Miracles","leadsTo":"dashboard"},{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part I","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":403,"slugs":["lesson-1","nothing-i-see-means-anything"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Review II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":484,"slugs":["review-ii","introduction"]}},{"label":"Lesson 85","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":489,"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-85"]}}],"slugs":["review-ii","lesson-85"],"canonicalLink":"https://acim.org/acim/review-ii/lesson-85/en/s/489","link":"https://acim.org/acim/review-ii/lesson-85/en/s